  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) is proposing a new rule (Regulation W) to implement comprehensively sections 23A and 23B of the Federal Reserve Act. The proposed rule would combine statutory restrictions on transactions between a bank and its affiliates with numerous existing and proposed Board interpretations and exemptions in an effort to simplify compliance with sections 23A and 23B.",
